annotation.TEXT: So, next time, I'll be playing 4-1-4, which'll be another boss level!
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marisa World! Now, I'm revisiting 0-1-2 here because Mark D pointed out something to me...
...Well. All that was in there was a white guy that died instantly. Very funny, game.
Be sure to grab the miko suit while over here, since it lets you destroy the Chomps in the broom room. Also, you should have 45 stars upon getting the miko suit.
DOUBLE KILL!
That was close. If I lost my broom there, that would've been annoying, and I would've gone to ludicrous speed with the footage as I went to get another broom.
Gotta check every dead end...
Alright, I've restarted the game, and... Oh, yeah. I'm above 5 million now!
Well, there goes a miko suit. Doesn't matter this time, since I'd prefer to keep the broom now.
Okay, there appear to be many ways to go. I guess I'll start exploring on the left first.
The Chomps could be a thing, though. I've had a few deaths to them. Just be careful and hope you don't get unlucky.
Alright, so let me just finish weaving my way through the Lay's Wavy guys and other blue duders here...
Pfft. Another dud.
Alright, so let's resume our exploration of the Scarlet Devil Mansion, with world 4-1-3!
Whoops. I wonder if I was supposed to follow that platform down...
Smack!
Okay, but I do see that P block, which probably has something I want. However, I have to get myself out of this sticky situation I got myself into first!
Alright, let's proceed to a later part of the level...
Oh, and this Rex does that thing again, where it gets shoved through the block by the Chomp. By this point, I've stopped trying to kill the Chomp, mainly due to this.
Nuts, more dud P blocks, and I'm not going to bother trying for that miko suit on the left side of this area at this point.
Oh, whoops! The game just crashed!
Die, Rex! Okay, the P block is at the end of this corridor. Right now, I'd probably prefer a miko suit, but I'd be okay with a broom as well.
Smack! Nailed that Chuck!
Didn't quite line up in time there. Well, I'll just proceed to the next one.
Okay, so here, kill the Chomps, grab all of the stars in the "1" and "2", and get the broom.
Pipe #3 leads to a nasty area with moving platforms and blue duders, and it begins with a cheap shot from a white FOE appearing right next to you when you emerge.
Next, grab all of the stars in the "3", but DO NOT enter the enterable pipe over here, and DO NOT get hit, as the P block here is dud, and you need to keep your broom.
I get jammed in it. However, I'm not really stuck. Pressing left or right will cause me to be expelled in the opposite direction.
Yeek!
I need to either Wiggler bounce or fly to get up here.
I see some stars over there in the shape of a "3", and I can guess how I'd reach those...
There's a large number 1 and a couple of dead Chomps.
Better not fall here, for obvious reasons.
I don't know why I didn't just complete the level there. Maybe because I was a bit annoyed at the time.
Well, that totally just happened. And yeah, that's what Mark D pointed out to me. The game can crash when you do this (though apparently only sometimes).
Uh, oh. I'm running low on time here.
Careful...
Ah, another pipe.
That was a high-up checkpoint there.
And now, let's start out by checking out pipe #1.
Aw, nuts! I was hoping to get up there by bouncing off of that blue guy... Now that angry Wiggler has me cornered, and I can't despawn it. I'll need a perfect jump to clear it...
Some of my fails were due to dumb deaths, but some of them were due to me being unable to find certain stars for a while. However, I've now found where they all are.
Another Chomp, but there's a handy blue guy right there.
Yep, I can clobber that guy way over there too. Now for this pipe...
Bah, how did I not jump there?
I don't think any one element of this level is too terribly difficult. It's just a matter of knowing where to go and not screwing up anywhere along the way.
And there are no stars to be found through pipe #3 anyway. Okay, so after collecting the "3" stars there, fly/hover back to where you got the broom.
Whoa, lucky stomp there. I didn't intend to hit my head on that ledge as I tried to jump around it there. Anyway, be sure to get the 4 stars over this pipe, of course.
And fly up and enter pipe #2. You should have 90 stars at this point.
And it turned out I didn't need him, but I still used him to destroy the Wiggler.
Stupid Chuck! I couldn't predict his trajectory there. I really hope I didn't absolutely need that broom...
I keep pulling that brief vanishing act whenever I try to drill stomp but hit down just as I land.
Alright, I'm going to show the whole run this time, without cutting anything out.
13 attempts later...
I'm not seeing any stars around here. Where could those remaining 22 stars be?
Okay, first of all, let's hit a B switch (I'm not going to bother mentioning presidents here, BTW).
Hey, potato chip, help me out here!
Oh, okay. Following that first platform was perfectly safe.
And that's because I would've likely tried pipe #1 first, and as I showed earlier, that's not the correct route if you're going for a perfect.
There's a Chomp here. Is there anything I can use to take it out?
That was a risky move.
Don't forget about these four stars that are on the way to the dud P block down here.
Awesome, a broom! Okay, now since this pipe back here is two-way, and there was a spot earlier where I said I'd need a broom to go further, well... You do the math.
Well, I'll hover down with the broom and hope for the best.
Okay, Chomp... I don't want any trouble. I just want to carefully slip past you...
Okay, the route I take up until I reach the broom is the same as the first run, but I want to point out an oddity that occurred fairly close to the start.
Tyler!
Okay, I wonder why Marisa turns invisible sometimes if I duck as I'm landing...
Whoa, geez. Treacherous jumps on ice blocks...
Oh, there we go! That one's no dud! Now I can rain death down upon all!
Interesting... I wonder if I can break any levels by doing that...
Yep, it just got shoved through that solid block by the Chomp. That actually screwed me up once, when I tried to kill the Chomp with the blue guy, and hit Rex instead.
7 attempts later...
What if I duck jump so that I'm up against the ceiling when the blocks come back?
Argh, really?! I'm stuck in the goal room, and can't go back for the stars I missed?! Darn it!
Game crash count: 1
Okay, time to fly!
Okay, pay attention to this Rex FOE right here.
...takes me back here. I kinda suspected it would do that. Alright, let's take that upper route now.
Okay, let's check out what's to the right from here...
However, I doubt I would've had a first-try perfect even if I didn't double back for the path that led to the secret exit.
Oh, I'm at the normal exit, but I'm still missing 22 stars... Oh, please tell me that I can enter at least one of these pipes...
Whoa, was I just standing on air for a split-second there? That was weird.
Yeah, I see a couple of potentially usable duders. Also, I see stars up above.
Clunk! He's gone.
Whoa, geez! Oh, the secret exit! Well, that's a pleasant surprise, and would explain why I haven't been seeing any stars along this route!
Okay, I'm not falling for that Thwomp again.
Another Chomp, but I'm already armed to deal with him.
I see more stars above, but there's that pipe below...
Whoa, geez! Okay, that Thwomp was just there to scare me, I guess. It wouldn't have hit me unless I moved left into it for whatever dumb reason.
Death from above!
Huh. I'm somewhere outside the mansion now.
Okay, let's go back for the normal exit and hopefully the perfect too...
To proceed further to the right, I'd probably need a broom. And this pipe...
Now, what happens if I'm overlapping a green block wall as it resolidifies?
Aw, but I can't enter it. Must be an exit from somewhere.
This place is definitely maze-like. Finding all the stars might be a chore.
Now, with the broom, take off and fly to the right here! Oh, and you might want to be ready to hover a little bit after the flight ends, just to be sure you make it.
Such a busy area with lots of different enemies...
Okay, I still want to go that way, in the hopes that that path leads to the P block.
Yes, I managed to escape!
Now, go back and hit the B switch. It's okay if you lose the broom at this point, as long as you don't fall or die. (If you fall from here, you end up in pipe #3's area. Not fun.)
And a number 2. Well, I think I know what I would've used for this episode's subtitle if I didn't show off that crash.
I suppose if you simply want to clear the level, and don't care about getting a perfect, pipe #1 is a good choice, but going that way forfeits 10 stars that are on another route.
Oh, it's two-way. I will remember this.
Well, it matters not, because those were the last 4 stars, and this pipe takes me straight to the goal!
Okay, now I'll just cut to when I reach the broom room.
There's a Rex, which I'll destroy.
Okay, here we are. First, let's murder the Chomps as usual, and then get the broom.
So, yeah. I know where all the stars are now. It's just a matter of getting them all without dying at this point.
Yeah, I was guessing that there were green dudes in those pipes.
GAAAMMMEEE!!! I wonder if all P blocks in this level are duds...
To be continued... Ze!
There's ice here too. Be careful.
I'm gonna clear out a few of these bricks first, but it's probably not really important. The time you have for this B switch run isn't really super-strict.
So yeah, basically, I had the initial route up to the broom room correct from my very first run.
Be careful. I have had deaths to the Blue Man Group here because of my recklessness.
Oh, come on! That was a really cheap Thwomp placement, above the camera like that.
HARRY UP!
DO NOT hit that B switch right away. First, go to the right and fly up for 6 stars.
